# Design identity (FigJam + brief)

## Creative direction (locked)

- **First impression:** **Exclusive, cool, niche** — not generic “festival hype”; visitors should feel they found something **select**, not mass-market.
- **Production mode:** **Commercial festival polish** (big production, high craft) with **alternative references** and **underground roots** — polished surface, credible subcultural DNA.
- **Place:** **Berlin** — urban, warehouse-adjacent, European electronic context (name locations in copy when useful; city is canonical).
- **Photography:** **Urban texture** + **crowd / high energy** — not only portraits; mix gritty context with peak-time floor energy.
- **Primary accent (if one only):** **Magenta** — lead brand signal for hero, key rails, and spine UI; other accents (acid green, yellow, cyan/teal) are **supporting** — use for structure/channels/digital chrome, not competing magenta moments on the same surface.
- **Brand motif (▲ / arrow-in-circle):** **Not used** — dropped; do not reintroduce unless explicitly requested.

## Positioning

- **Look:** **Modern, commercial, innovative** — editorial/fashion energy (bold art direction), not a default Bootstrap landing page.
- **Keywords:** **Typographic/sans-serif**, **maximal**, **bold**, **multicultural**, **well-designed**, **young**, **cool**, **urban**, **digital**, **color contrast**.
- **Palette:** **Black & white** foundation + **magenta-led** accents + controlled supporting ladder: **acid green / yellow** for day splits or secondary drama **one hot accent per major band** where needed; **cyan/teal** = tertiary **digital chrome only** (grids, cursor trail, annotations, halftone tint) — avoid large cyan fields.

## Typography system (locked)

- **Editorial-first:** **Zalando Sans Expanded** (variable, self-hosted via Fontsource) = **display** — hero headlines, lineup act names, large section titles, rave-photo overlays.
- **Inter** = **body + UI** — paragraphs, eyebrows, ticker, table headers/meta, labels, buttons.
- **Noto Sans** (JP / KR / Arabic from Google Fonts) = **script fallback** for decorative/expression layers and any mixed-script UI; do not add a fourth Latin family.

## Typography & layout

- **Heavy sans-serif** grotesk / neo-grotesk feel (delivered by **Expanded** width + weight); type as **graphic object** — **overlap**, **stack**, **rotate**, **huge headlines**, not only body copy.
- **Grid-aware** and **asymmetric** layouts OK; **grain / noise**, **scanlines**, **glitch lines**, **terminal/code** motifs are on-brand when used with intent.
- **References (mood, not to copy assets):** Mechatok — *Expression On Your Face* (cyber-urban, barcode/UI texture); **[i-D](https://i-d.co/)**-style **editorial** boldness and youth culture framing.

## Signature components (build toward these)

1. **Hero** — photographic or typographic dominance; **tinted** B&W + **accent** lasers or UI chrome; optional **text-mask** or **reflection** effects.
2. **News ticker / marquee** — **horizontal** strip, **looping rave/party headlines** (icons OK), feels like **broadcast / club flyer** energy.
3. **Interactive type zones** — **pointer-driven** rearrangement or **physics-like** text behavior; optional **mouse-trail characters** (+, o, x, <, >, etc.) in small boxes or glyphs.
4. **Pretext-driven blocks** — dense or **particle-like** typographic fields where **layout stays fast** (measure with Pretext, animate deliberately).
5. **3D graffiti panels** (later) — **exhibition** walkthrough vibe; **Three.js**-style scene, **client-only**.

## Motion & sound

- **Motion:** **Sharp, energetic, digital** — snaps, quick eases, glitch-adjacent cuts; not soft cinematic drift as default. **Section transitions** can be **full-scene**. Always pair with **`prefers-reduced-motion`** fallbacks for decorative motion.
- **Audio:** **Club system** — punchy, full-range, “PA in a room” character when playing; **respect autoplay policy** — clear user control to opt in; never hide critical info in audio alone.
